  <title translate="true">Tip #57</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Writing STB conversions can be made easier by following certain simple rules:</text></para>
          <list id="1" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px; font-family:Symbol; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Always add new instance variables after existing ones.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Avoid reordering existing instance variables.</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Don&apos;t remove existing variables (just reserve them for later use).</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Normal" style="margin-left:24px;"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">Why not reserve a few extra instance variable slots for use at a later date.</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
